data.title: St Joseph's Church, Brighton
data.meta_description: St Joseph's Church is a Grade II listed Roman Catholic church in the city of Brighton and Hove. Unlike other churches, the architecture of this church is very unique, and it rightly acknowledged for its architectural importance by the English Heritage. It was an erstwhile Anglican church before it was converted into a Roman Catholic and making it the part of the only eleven Roman Catholic churches in Brighton and Hove. Visit the website for more details on the history of the church.
